__NAME__ purpose
specify Interchange log output filename
__END__


__NAME__ missing
__END__


__NAME__ synopsis
<arg choice='plain'><replaceable>filename</replaceable></arg>
__END__


__NAME__ description
Specify &glos-catalog; log file. If the filename is not absolute,
it is treated relative to the catalog root directory (&glos-CATROOT;).
</para><para>
The file will gather output of the
<function>::logData()</function> function.
__END__

__NAME__ see also
ErrorFile, DebugFile
__END__

__NAME__ notes
This directive only specifies the default log file. The &tag-log; tag accepts
parameter <option>file</option> to use other destinations.
__END__

__NAME__ example: Setting __FILENAME__
<programlisting>
LogFile etc/catlog
</programlisting>
__END__

